<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-11-13T00:35:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-11-13T00:35:00-05:00" n="425" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d425">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">123 D 82/567: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-11-13T09:00:00+03:25">November
                                    13, 1943—9 a.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 9:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1059. Referring to my telegram No. 1045, November 4, 9 a.m. I returned
                            Tehran yesterday from Marrakesh and resumed charge of the Legation
                            today, This change in my plans was made after consultation with
                            Secretary Hull who suggested the advisability of postponing my leave for
                            a few weeks pending a more suitable moment.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Dreyfus</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>